## Plan gate (attempt 1) — Tier 1 four-seat: BLOCK (1 GO / 3 BLOCK)
- pi/pilms: GO. Claude Opus: BLOCK; Gemini Pro: BLOCK; GPT-5.5 xhigh (codex): BLOCK — converged required changes:
  1. (.etude/ COLLISION — Opus+Gemini+codex) materializing inputs to .etude/inputs/ + output to .etude/output INSIDE the checked-out worktree collides with the REAL .etude/ config (workflow.yaml, evals/) present in every checked-out commit of this repo (NOT gitignored). Move replay scratch I/O OUT of the worktree into an external scratch dir; keep the detached worktree BYTE-IDENTICAL to the recorded commit (the GitSHA is the provenance anchor — mutating the tree breaks the match).
  2. (OUTPUT MEDIA TYPE — codex) the exec runner cannot infer media type from an extensionless output file, and artifactstore.AddContent REQUIRES a media type. RunRequest must carry OutputMediaType (from ResolvedStage.Output.MediaType); RunResult.MediaType defaults to it.

## PLAN AMENDMENT (incorporated for gate attempt 2)
- RunRequest{ WorktreeDir (the PRISTINE detached checkout == recorded GitSHA, read-only for the skill), ScratchDir (external os.MkdirTemp dir where phase2.4 materializes inputs + reads output — NEVER inside the worktree), Inputs []RunInput, OutputRole string, OutputMediaType string (from the original stage Output.MediaType), Skill runmanifest.Skill }.
- RunResult{ Output []byte, MediaType string (defaults to req.OutputMediaType; runner may override), Skill runmanifest.Skill }.
- File convention (DOCUMENTED here, IMPLEMENTED in phase2.4 exec runner): inputs at <ScratchDir>/inputs/<NN>-<role>, output at <ScratchDir>/output. The worktree stays clean.
- StubRunner: uses ONLY the in-memory Inputs (NO FS, NO exec); canned + concat (documented separator/order) modes; injectable error; echoes req.Skill into RunResult.Skill; RunResult.MediaType defaults to req.OutputMediaType. This bead = interface + value types + stub; materialization is phase2.4 — keep this bead's tests FS-free.
- Docs in code comments: RunRequest.Inputs are always fully-materialized content bytes (pointers rejected pre-run via ErrPointerNotMaterialized); RunResult.Skill MAY differ from RunRequest.Skill (the new replay skill identity — the whole point); compile-time var _ Runner = (*StubRunner)(nil).
